# SPDX-License-Identifier: Apache-2.0 WITH LLVM-exception
#
# test/Fmt/smoke.test — Phase-1 sentinel fixture for the nsl-fmt lit
# corpus. Exists so `lit /work/test/Fmt` finds at least one test and
# does not error out with "did not discover any tests" before Phase 3
# fixtures land. Per `test/lit.cfg.py` the auto-discovery picks up any
# `.test` file recursively — when Phase 3 starts adding real fixtures
# under `test/Fmt/rules/`, `test/Fmt/cli/`, etc., they are discovered
# automatically with no edits to this file.
#
# This fixture's RUN line is intentionally trivial — it asserts only
# that lit + the shell are wired (Phase-1 checkpoint per
# `quickstart.md` §3 T-1: "ninja check-nsl-fmt runs zero tests
# successfully" — clarified during /speckit-implement to mean "runs
# at least one trivially-passing test", because lit refuses to run
# zero tests).

# RUN: true
# CHECK: any-pattern-not-required-for-trivial-RUN
